content.webTitle: Led Zeppelin formed by Jimmy Page

fields.headline: Led Zeppelin formed by Jimmy Page
fields.bodyText: Back in 1968, Jimmy Page was a hard-nosed rhythm'n'blues session musician. When his then band the Yardbirds split, with a swathe of tour dates yet to play, Page assembled an outfit from acquaintances of acquaintances. And so arguably the greatest rock band of all time – Led Zeppelin – began as the New Yardbirds on a Scandinavian tour undertaken to escape lawsuits from irate promoters; with a bustle, rather than a bang.
